{"lemma":"بُلْه","slug":"بُلْه","root":"ب.ل.ه","root_slug":"ب-ل-ه","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ل-ه","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["name"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3101","n3109","n3110","n3111","n3271","n3276","n3277","n44427"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8F%D9%84%D9%92%D9%87"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"name","gloss":"Ávila (a province of Castile and León, Spain; capital: Ávila)"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Ávila (a city in Ávila, Castile and León, Spain)"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʔaː.bi.la/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3101","headword_ar":"بَلَّهُ","root":"bl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~N","text_ar":"بَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bil~apN","text_ar":"بِلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He moistened it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) with water (M, Msb, K) &c.; (M;) and in like manner, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bl~lhu","text_ar":"بلّلهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) but signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he moistened it much."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) ―         -b2- [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~ati AlA_ibilu A^agomaArahaA","text_ar":"بَلَّتِ الاـِبِلُ اَغْمَارَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camels damped their thirst;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drank a little."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gmr","text_ar":"غمر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~a raHimahu","text_ar":"بَلَّ رَحِمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~N","text_ar":"بَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(with fet-h, TA [in the CK it has kesr]) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bilaAlN","text_ar":"بِلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made close"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he refreshed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his ties of relationship by behaving with goodness and affection and gentleness to his kindred;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waSalahaA","text_ar":"وَصَلَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nad~aAhaA","text_ar":"نَدَّاهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T:) for, as some things are conjoined and commixed by moisture, and become disunited by dryness,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~N","text_ar":"بَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is metaphorically used to denote conjunction, as above, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yubosN","text_ar":"يُبْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to denote the contrary. (TA.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waAlr~iHoma fA@bolulohaA bixayori Albul~aAno\n                      \n                     \n                        faA_inahaAA@$otuq~ato mini A@somi Alr~aHom`no"},{"kind":"text","text":"[(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the ties of relationship, make thou them close &c. by the best mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"modes, of doing so; for the name thereof is derived from the name of the Compassionate"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: here ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albul~aAn","text_ar":"البُلَّان"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be a noun in the sing. number, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guforaAnN","text_ar":"غُفْرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or it may be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balalN","text_ar":"بَلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which may be either a subst. or an. inf. n., for some inf. ns. have pls., as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ugolN","text_ar":"شُغْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqolN","text_ar":"عَقْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraDN","text_ar":"مَرَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) And it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bul~uwA A^aroHaAmakumo walawo biAls~alaAmi","text_ar":"بُلُّوا اَرْحَامَكُمْ وَلَوْ بِالسَّلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Make ye close"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refresh ye"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"your ties of relationship &c., though but,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"if only, by salutation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiluwhaA","text_ar":"صِلُوهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nad~uwhaA biAlS~ilapi","text_ar":"نَدُّوهَا بِالصِّلَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) And hence the saying in another trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*a A@sota$an~a maA bayonaka wa bayona A@ll~`hi faA@bolulohu","text_ar":"اـِذَ ا@سْتَشَنَّ مَا بَيْنَكَ وَ بَيْنَ ا@للّٰهِ فَا@بْلُلْهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlA_iHosaAni A_ilaY EibaAdahi","text_ar":"بِالاـِحْسَانِ اـِلَى عِبَادَهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When the tie between thee and God wears out, repair thou it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refresh thou it, by beneficence to his servants"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bilaAlN","text_ar":"بِلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~aka A@ll~`hu biA@bonK","text_ar":"بَلَّكَ ا@للّٰهُ بِا@بْنٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bonFA","text_ar":"ا@بْنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God give thee a son."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K, TA.) Hence, perhaps, the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bul~ato yadaAka bihi","text_ar":"بُلَّتْ يَدَاكَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou was given it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 479.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balalotuhu","text_ar":"بَلَلْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I gave to him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA taboluka EinodiY baAl~apN","text_ar":"لَا تَبْلُكَ عِنْدِى بَالَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balaAlN","text_ar":"بَلَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, K, [but in the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinodanaA","text_ar":"عِنْدَنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and “ or ” for “ and, ” and in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA tabal~uka","text_ar":"لا تَبَلُّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"No bounty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"no good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"no benefit, shall betide thee from me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor will I profit thee, nor believe thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~uwA","text_ar":"بَلُّوا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They sowed"},{"kind":"text","text":"land. (ISh, T, K.)       -A2-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~a","text_ar":"بَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an intrans. verb perhaps primarily signifies"},{"kind":"page_break","n":243},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, moist;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and has for its sec. pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balilota","text_ar":"بَلِلْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balalota","text_ar":"بَلَلْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and for its aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"text","text":", and for its inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balalN","text_ar":"بَلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and probably"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bil~apN","text_ar":"بِلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. mentioned with that noun below. ―         -b2-  And hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~ati Alr~iyHu","text_ar":"بَلَّتِ الرِّيحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buluwlN","text_ar":"بُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wind was cold and moist."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baliylN","text_ar":"بَلِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  [And hence, probably, as though originally said of one who had had a fever,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~a mino maraDihi","text_ar":"بَلَّ مِنْ مَرَضِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~N","text_ar":"بَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balalN","text_ar":"بَلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buluwlN","text_ar":"بُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abl~","text_ar":"ابلّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astbl~","text_ar":"استبلّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He recovered from his disease:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abtl~","text_ar":"ابتلّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tbl~l","text_ar":"تبلّل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became in a good condition after leanness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meagerness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,Z:) or all have this latter signification: and the second ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abl~","text_ar":"ابلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":") has the former also. (K.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~a","text_ar":"بَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buluwlN","text_ar":"بُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abl~","text_ar":"ابلّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"escaped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became safe"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"secure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from difficulty, distress,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"straitness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~a fiY AlA^aroD","text_ar":"بَلَّ فِى الاَرْض"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K, * TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~N","text_ar":"بَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abl~","text_ar":"ابلّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went away in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into, the land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"country."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~ato naAqatuhu","text_ar":"بَلَّتْ نَاقَتُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His she-camel went away."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~ato","text_ar":"بَلَّتْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTiy~atuhu EalaY wajohihaA","text_ar":"مَطِيَّتُهُ عَلَى وَجْهِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, T, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ElY","text_ar":"على"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abl~t","text_ar":"ابلّت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wjhA","text_ar":"وجها"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"riding-camel, ran away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went away, at random, to pasture, straying;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hamato DaAl~apF","text_ar":"هَمَتْ ضَالَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Fr, T, K, TA. [In the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hmt","text_ar":"همت"},{"kind":"text","text":", which, as is said in the TA, is without teshdeed, is written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ham~ato","text_ar":"هَمَّتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balilotu minohu","text_ar":"بَلِلْتُ مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (As, T, S, &c.,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balalN","text_ar":"بَلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I got him; got possession of him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, T, S, M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"got him in my hand."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lay^ino bal~ato bika yadiY laA","text_ar":"لَيِنْ بَلَّتْ بِكَ يَدِى لَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tufaAriquniY A^awo tuw^ad~iYa Haq~iY","text_ar":"تُفَارِقُنِى اَوْ تُوَدِّىَ حَقِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Assuredly if my hand get hold of thee, thou shalt not quit me unless thou give up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pay, my right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And hence the prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA balalotu mino fulaAnK biA^afowaqa naASilK","text_ar":"مَا بَلَلْتُ مِنْ فُلَانٍ بِاَفْوَقَ نَاصِلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I did not get, in such a one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a man like"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an arrow with a broken notch"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without a head"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning I got a perfect man; one sufficient. (Sh, T.) ―         -b2-  Also, (T,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balilotuhu","text_ar":"بَلِلْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I kept,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clave, to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K,) namely, a man, (T, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and constantly associated with him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~a","text_ar":"بَلَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAl$~ayo'i","text_ar":"بِالشَّيْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~N","text_ar":"بَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became devoted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attached, to the thing, and kept to it constantly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balilotu minohu","text_ar":"بَلِلْتُ مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balalN","text_ar":"بَلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balaAlapN","text_ar":"بَلَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buluwlN","text_ar":"بُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I was tried by him (muniytu bihi [app. meaning biHub~ihi by love of him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and loved him"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealiqotuhu","text_ar":"عَلِقْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealaqotuhu","text_ar":"عَلَقْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]); as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balalotu bh","text_ar":"بَلَلْتُ به"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AA, M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buluwlN","text_ar":"بُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balilotu bihi","text_ar":"بَلِلْتُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I was tried by him, as though by fire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Saliytu bh","text_ar":"صَلِيتُ به"},{"kind":"text","text":", [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Salayotu","text_ar":"صَلَيْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and suffered distress,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"misery,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fatigue"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqiytu","text_ar":"شَقِيتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ufiytu","text_ar":"شُفِيتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put in the copies of the K: TA). (M, K. *) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA balalotu bihi","text_ar":"مَا بَلَلْتُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balalN","text_ar":"بَلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I did not light on,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meet with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"find, nor know, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it; expl. by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^aSabotuhu wa laA Ealimotuhu","text_ar":"مَا اَصَبْتُهُ وَ لَا عَلِمْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~a","text_ar":"بَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Th, M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balalN","text_ar":"بَلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Th, S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abal~","text_ar":"اَبَلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which epithet see below]. (Th, S, M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Msb","K","T","TA","Z","Fr","AA","Th"]},{"entry_id":"n3109","headword_ar":"بَلَّةٌ","root":"bl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A single act of moistening."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b2-  And hence,] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"least sprinkling"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adonaY balalK","text_ar":"اَدْنَى بَلَلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"least moisture"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of good."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hl","text_ar":"هل"},{"kind":"text","text":".) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='anaA","text_ar":"جَا=ءَنَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN falamo yaA^otinaA bihal~apK walaA bal~apK","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ فَلَمْ يَاْتِنَا بِهَلَّةٍ وَلَا بَلَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one came to us and did not bring us anything to rejoice us nor the least sprinkling of good"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hl~p","text_ar":"هلّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to ISK, being from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaraHu","text_ar":"الفَرَحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAisotiholaAlu","text_ar":"الاِسْتِهْلَالُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bl~p","text_ar":"بلّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albalolu","text_ar":"البَلْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxayoru","text_ar":"الخَيْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^aSaAba hal~apF","text_ar":"مَا اَصَابَ هَلَّةً"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA bal~apF","text_ar":"وَلَا بَلَّةً"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He did not obtain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has not obtained, anything."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"competence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"competence, after poverty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, T, K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bul~aY","text_ar":"بُلَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Remains of herbage"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pasture;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bul~apN","text_ar":"بُلَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Fr, T, K.) ―         -b5-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"freshness"},{"kind":"text","text":"of youth; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bul~apN","text_ar":"بُلَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K; *) but the former word is the more approved. (M.) ―         -b6-  See also an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balalN","text_ar":"بَلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Fr","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n3110","headword_ar":"بُلَّةٌ","root":"bl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balalN","text_ar":"بَلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places: ―         -b2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bal~apN","text_ar":"بَلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A state of moisture."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b4-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moisture of fresh pasture."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K.) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rájiz"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Iháb Ibn-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"'Omeyr,"},{"kind":"text","text":"TA) says, describing [wild] asses,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wa faAraqatohaA bul~apu AlA^awaAbili \n                      \n                     \n                        Hat~aY A_i*aA A^ahoraA^ona biAlA^aSaAy^ili"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning that they went in the cool of the evening to the water after that the herbage had dried up:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAwAbl","text_ar":"الاوابل"},{"kind":"text","text":"means the wild animals that are satisfied with green pasture, so as to be in no need of water. (S.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3111","headword_ar":"بِلَّةٌ","root":"bl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balalN","text_ar":"بَلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Good, good fortune, prosperity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wealth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sustenance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"means of subsistence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Health; soundness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"freedom from disease."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A repast prepared on the occasion of a wedding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on any occasion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, K.) ―         -b5-  (tropical:)  The tongue's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fluency, and chasteness of speech:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or its"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"readiness of diction"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expression, and facility;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so in the M, but in the K “ or, ”]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its falling upon the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"places of utterance of the letters,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and its regular and uniform continuance of speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and its facility."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^aHosanN bil~apa lisaAnihi","text_ar":"مَا اَحْسَنٌ بِلَّةَ لِسَانِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How good is the fluency, &c., of his tongue!"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T, M, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","T","M","A"]},{"entry_id":"n3271","headword_ar":"بَلِهَ","root":"blh","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balahN","text_ar":"بَلَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * Msb, K, * TA,) [and irregularly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balaAhapN","text_ar":"بَلَاهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bulahoniyapN","text_ar":"بُلَهْنِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balahN","text_ar":"بَلَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below,)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abolah","text_ar":"اَبْلَه"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tbl~h","text_ar":"تبلّه","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abtlh","text_ar":"ابتله","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, weak in intellect."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was unable to adduce his argument, proof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evidence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of his heedlessness, and his smallness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lack, of discrimination."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n3276","headword_ar":"بَلْهَ","root":"blh","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is an indecl. word with fet-h for its termination, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayofa","text_ar":"كَيْفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEo","text_ar":"دَعْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Let alone,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"say nothing of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S;) [i. e.] it is a noun for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEo","text_ar":"دَعْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; indecl.; (Mughnee, K;) a verbal noun, meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEo","text_ar":"دَعْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^utoruko","text_ar":"اُتْرُكْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IAth, TA;) and the noun that"},{"kind":"page_break","n":254},{"kind":"text","text":"follows it, when it is thus used, is in the accus. case; (Mughnee, K;) i. e. it is indecl., with fet-h for its termination, when the noun following it is in the accus. case; so that you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baloha zayodFA","text_ar":"بَلْهَ زَيْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Let alone Zeyd,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"say nothing of Zeyd"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; like as you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruwayoda zayodFA","text_ar":"رُوَيْدَ زَيْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IB, TA:) and it is also an inf. n. in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~aroku","text_ar":"التَّرْكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; likewise with fet-h for its termination, but decl.; and when it is thus used, the noun that follows it is in the gen. case; (Mughnee, K;) or it is put in the place of an inf. n., meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taroka","text_ar":"تَرْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is virtually the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Autoruko","text_ar":"اُتْرُكْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEo","text_ar":"دَعْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and is prefixed to a noun in the gen. case; so that you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baloha zayodK","text_ar":"بَلْهَ زَيْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taroka zayodK","text_ar":"تَرْكَ زَيْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is virtually the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baloha zayodFA","text_ar":"بَلْهَ زَيْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"explained above; for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taroka zayodK","text_ar":"تَرْكَ زَيْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Autoruko zayodFA tarokFA","text_ar":"اُتْرُكْ زَيْدًا تَرْكًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDaroba Alr~iqaAbi","text_ar":"فَضَرْبَ الرِّقَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur xlvii. 4 is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fA@DoribuwA Alr~iqaAba","text_ar":"فا@ضْرِبُوا الرِّقَابَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DarobFA","text_ar":"ضَرْبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (IAth, TA;) for in this case it cannot be regarded as a verbal noun, since verbal nouns are not prefixed to other nouns, governed by them in the gen. case: (IB, TA:) and it is also a noun syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayofa","text_ar":"كَيْفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; likewise with fet-h for its termination, indecl.; and when it is thus used, the noun that follows it is in the nom. case. (Mughnee, K.) A poet says, describing swords, (S, Mughnee,) namely, Kaab Ibn-Málik, (S,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"ta*aru AljamaAjima DaAHiyFA haAmatuhaA\n                      \n                     \n                        baloha AlA^akuf~a kaA^an~ahaA lamo tuxolaqi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They leave the skulls with their crowns lying open to the sun (let alone,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"say nothing of, the hands) as though they had not been created"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, Mughnee:) he says, when they cut, or cut off, the crowns, then let alone, or say nothing of, the hands ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fadaEi AlA^akuf~a","text_ar":"فَدَعِ الاَكُفَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): i. e., they are more fit for cutting off the hands: (TA:) Akh says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"blh","text_ar":"بله"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here in the place of an inf. n.; that it is as when you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Daroba zayodK","text_ar":"ضَرْبَ زَيْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAkf~","text_ar":"الاكفّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be in the accus. case; so that the meaning may be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEi AlA^akuf~a","text_ar":"دَعِ الاَكُفَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) the verse is thus recited in two different ways: and also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baloha AlA^akuf~u","text_ar":"بَلْهَ الاَكُفُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"how"},{"kind":"text","text":"then must be the case of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the hands?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mughnee.) And hence the prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuHoriquka Aln~aAru A_ino taraAhaA baloha A^ano","text_ar":"تُحْرِقُكَ النَّارُ اـِنْ تَرَاهَا بَلْهَ اَنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSolaAhaA","text_ar":"تَصْلَاهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fire will burn thee if thou see it"},{"kind":"text","text":"from a distance:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"then let alone,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"say nothing of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fadaEo","text_ar":"فَدَعْ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy entering into it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) A strange instance occurs in the Saheeh of El-Bukháree, in the explanation of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=l=m=","text_ar":"ا=ل=م="},{"kind":"text","text":"of the chapter of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ajodap","text_ar":"السَّجْدَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the 32nd ch. of the Kur]: he says, God says [by these three letters],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEodadotu liEibaAdiy","text_ar":"اَعْدَدْتُ لِعِبَادِي"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~aAliHiyna maA laA EayonN raA^ato walaA A^u*unN samiEato wa laA xaTari","text_ar":"الصَّالِحِينَ مَا لَا عَيْنٌ رَاَتْ وَلَا اُذُنٌ سَمِعَتْ وَ لَا خَطَرِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY qalobi ba$arK *uxorFA mino balohi maA A@T~alaEotumo Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَى قَلْبِ بَشَرٍ ذُخْرًا مِنْ بَلْهِ مَا ا@طَّلَعْتُمْ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mughnee, K: *) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA A^aTalaEotuhumo Ealayohi","text_ar":"ما اَطَلَعْتُهُمْ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (so in some copies of the K:) thus"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"blh","text_ar":"بله"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as a decl. word, governed in the gen. case by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn","text_ar":"من"},{"kind":"text","text":", and deviating from the three meanings [explained above]: (Mughnee, K:) but the reading commonly known is,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ElY qlb b$r baloha ma A^aTolaEotuhumo Elyh","text_ar":"على قلب بشر بَلْهَ مَ اَطْلَعْتُهُمْ عليه"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and this is the reading in the work of J, [the S,] and in the Nh, and other lexicological works: (TA:) it has been explained by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gayor","text_ar":"غَيْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [so that the meaning of the sentence as first related above is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have prepared for my righteous servants what eye hath not seen, nor ear heard, nor hath it occurred to the mind of man, as a treasure for the future,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(obviously taken from Isaiah lxiv. 4, quoted by St. Paul in 1 Cor. ii. 9,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"save,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"except, that with which ye have become acquainted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that with which I have acquainted them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the same, with the omission of “ as a treasure for the future, “ is the meaning of the sentence as related in the S and Nh &c.;] (Mughnee, K;) i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siwaY","text_ar":"سِوَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the S; (TA;) and this corroborates, (Mughnee,) or is agreeable with, (K,) the opinion of those who reckon"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"blh","text_ar":"بله"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an exceptive word: (Mughnee, K:) and as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajalo","text_ar":"اَجَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajol","text_ar":"اَجْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"; i. e., it has been explained also as meaning I have done all this because of my promise to them; ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino A^ajoli maA A^aTolaEotuhumo Ealayohi","text_ar":"مِنْ اَجْلِ مَا اَطْلَعْتُهُمْ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"because of that with which I have acquainted them;"},{"kind":"text","text":") and thus it may have been read by SM, for he has written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajl","text_ar":"اجل"},{"kind":"text","text":"without any syll. signs; and has given no other ex. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"blh","text_ar":"بله"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense here intended except one commencing with the words,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baloha An~iY lamo A^axuno","text_ar":"بَلْهَ انِّى لَمْ اَخُنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EahodFA","text_ar":"عَهْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", which may mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"because I have not broken a covenant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yea, verily I have not"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., accord. as we read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^an~iY","text_ar":"اَنِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~iY","text_ar":"اـِنِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuf~a","text_ar":"كُفَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuf~a Eano","text_ar":"كُفَّ عَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEo","text_ar":"دَعْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"let alone,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"say nothing of;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this explanation must relate to the sentence as given in the S and Nh]: (K, but omitted in an excellent copy of that work:) or, accord. to El-Ahmar, it means, in this trad. [as commonly known],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayufa","text_ar":"كَيُفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"how?"},{"kind":"text","text":"which seems to be the least suitable of all these explanations]. (TA.) IAmb relates, on the authority of others, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baloha","text_ar":"بَلْهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": [but I think that this is a mistake, arising from a misunderstanding of what here follows:] Fr says that he who makes it to govern a gen. case regards it as used in the manner of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and similar particles governing the gen. case. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA balohaka","text_ar":"مَا بَلْهَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA baAluka","text_ar":"مَا بَالُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is thy state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA laka","text_ar":"مَا لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which often has this meaning: see the letter"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (So in some copies of the K.)"}],"source_refs":["IB","TA","S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n3277","headword_ar":"بَلَهٌ","root":"blh","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balaAhapN","text_ar":"بَلَاهَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[both properly inf. ns.; see 1;] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attribute,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality, denoted by the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abolahN","text_ar":"اَبْلَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; (S, K;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heedlessness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heedlessness of evil;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK in explanation of the former, and K;) &c.; (K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bulahoniyapN","text_ar":"بُلَهْنِيَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stupidity and languor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK.)"}],"source_refs":["K"]},{"entry_id":"n44427","headword_ar":"بُلَةٌ","root":"wbl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibaAlapN","text_ar":"اـِبَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}